<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> -Concussion too difficult for the level of the spell</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I agree. It's a great spell. It's level 39, not because you can channel it better, or reduce fizzles. That's like saying Ice Comet is a level 49 spell, but we shouldn't get it until level 60. Hello retards!<br>
If it were up to me, I'd take out the CoM Skeleton and make that part into a miniquest. Something that would drag out that part a little longer, but be easier than the current system.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> -Not enough spells of types per level range (15 levels between ice spell or fire spells is not according to verant's stated design intent for the class)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I agree. I think Wizards should get spells every level instead of every 4 or 5. Think about it. Kunark gave us spells every level from 51-60. Why? Because they didn't want to give us more spells in lump sums.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> -Too many big gaps in AE spells (17 levels between pillar of frost and circle of force is too many)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I agree, but you're forgeting about gravity flux at 44 (teehee). Oh, you mean AoEs that we actually use? Well, that would probably mean it'd be easier to quad between those levels, which I can't see VI wanting. I really wish they'd make AoEs more useful in group situations. It would help us get groups, and also allow us to use our full potential.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> -Some levels Wizards have smaller blasts than other classes, if this is an acceptible design why isn't it true ALL levels, if its not why any levels at all, no matter how low?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I'm not quite sure which levels you're referring to, but I know some levels we're really close with other classes. Damage isn't the only thing to consider though. There is also cast time, and mana cost as well. Our nukes are superior to all other classes when you look at the whole picture.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> -Post 50 blasts absurdly clustered at level 60. Push sunstrike lower in levels</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Again, I agree. With the new ancient spells being introduced, people aren't going to use the lesser versions anymore. If it were up to me:<br>
<br>
Disintegrate would be moved to level 56.<br>
Sunstrike would be moved to level 57.<br>
Soloist's would be moved to level 58.<br>
Elnerick's would be moved to level 59.<br>
Garrison's would be the level 60 normal nuke (if it's ever found).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> -Ice Comet and Rend have damage increases that stop after 1 level, why? Even if Ice Comet kept increasing all the way to level 60 it would only do 1220 damage</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Yup, that's messed up. I think it's just the fact that they keep using the excuse that they're &quot;old world spells&quot; and since the level cap for those that never bought an expansion is still level 50, they don't see any need to make them scale to 60. Even though they're now putting level 50+ dungeons in the old world <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> -Why no personal port to south ro, only an evac?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Good question. It'd be nice if we had Gates, Trans, Evacs, and Portals to all the locations on Norrath and Luclin where there is a Spire/Pyramid. We don't even need all of those for each location, but not having all of those travel spells would further confuse people. Hell, I'd like a Gate to Shadowhaven, but I don't see that happening. But there is a portal there.<br>
They changed our portal system with Kunark. Then they changed it again with Velious, and yet again with Luclin. Why not stick to the original plan? Because they never had one. They toss them in at the last moment.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> -No nexus gate from outside Luclin, there's absolutely no defensible reason for this in game or role play terms</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The simple reason is this: If we could use our Luclin gates/TLs/Portals from anywhere, then it would make our levle 59 AA skill Nexus Gate useless. Of course a simple fix would be to make our level 59 AA skill Innate Gate, which would <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> take you to your bind spot</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, but that never occured to them.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> -Eye of Zomm aggro, negates its use as a scouting tool, did Verant INTEND for it only to be used to pull with?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Fixed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> -Eye of Zomm swims at 0 skill and is utterly worthless in water, this looks more like an oversight than intentional</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I like how you use the term &quot;role play terms&quot; when it suits your purpose, but don't use it when it won't work. It's an eyeball. Eyeballs can't swim without arms or something. At least in Role play terms.<br>
Honestly, I've only used Eye of Zohm a couple times, and it's only been since they fixed the aggro issues. I can't think of a place, besides Kedge, where you'd need to scout underwater. Maybe Siren's Grotto...<br>
I'd like it if they'd fix the eye so it looks like an eye, and not a black ball with red lines on it.<br>
<br>
Good summery Grim. <p><center>
